OL,7,FA NHS trust has apologised to a man
OL,8,Fwhose wife died "alone and in pain"
OL,9,Fafter admitting that reduced staffing
OL,10,Flevels on its wards played a
OL,11,F"significant" role in her death.
OL,13,FJohn Huggins was left devastated after
OL,14,Fbeing told his wife of 50 years,
OL,15,FJeanine, had passed away during the
OL,16,Fnight without him being by her side
OL,17,Ffollowing a series of failings at
OL,18,FNorfolk and Norwich University Hospital
OL,19,F(NNUH) earlier this year. She was 69.
OL,3,C'My wife was left to die alone and in
OL,4,Cpain on a busy NHS ward - how did that
OL,5,Chappen?'
